Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.40,0:00:02.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Adam.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.00,0:00:04.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eyes here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.79,0:00:07.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Follow my finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.03,0:00:09.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Adam.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.46,0:00:12.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Show me...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.70,0:00:14.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a bicycle.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.29,0:00:20.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eyes here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.66,0:00:27.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Adam.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.59,0:00:30.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Show me a bicycle.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.52,0:00:48.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, buddy, that's a ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.32,0:00:50.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Adam, look at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.48,0:00:52.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you hungry?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.53,0:00:55.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Show me what you want for lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.40,0:01:16.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still Drawing those lines instead of looking at the cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.48,0:01:21.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More juice?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.54,0:01:24.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he wants more juice, he has to ask for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.31,0:01:26.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Adam.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.68,0:01:28.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Buddy, eyes here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.20,0:01:29.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's tired, Dom.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.41,0:01:32.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't be if we stuck to the schedule.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.89,0:01:35.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Show me the juice, buddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.10,0:01:37.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think we've reached the point of diminishing returns.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.49,0:01:38.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He has to ask for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.99,0:01:40.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Adam.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.85,0:01:43.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's choking.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.38,0:01:46.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's impossible. It's mac and cheese.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.50,0:01:57.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,House S03E04\NLines in the Sand
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.48,0:02:29.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ten-year-old boy, screams for his life for no reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.89,0:02:30.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's autistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.82,0:02:33.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Severely autistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.49,0:02:35.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't talk, can't make eye contact.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.67,0:02:37.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Screaming's probably his way of communicating.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.00,0:02:40.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And he went to three different doctors who all said just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.38,0:02:43.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, so clearly, that can't be the answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.64,0:02:45.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His brain can't filter information.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.08,0:02:46.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a constant assault on his senses.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.80,0:02:48.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd scream too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.60,0:02:52.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or it's something medical sounding, like dysesthesia.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.12,0:02:55.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Parents are convinced that there's something wrong with their son.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.40,0:02:59.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since when did we start believing parents?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.16,0:02:59.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or anyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.97,0:03:01.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are we going?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.63,0:03:03.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Elevator.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.38,0:03:06.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad was on wall street, mom was a partner in an accounting firm.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.62,0:03:09.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When their son was diagnosed with autism, they both quit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.01,0:03:10.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So they're overprotective and scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.62,0:03:13.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all the more reason to discount-- they study this kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.18,0:03:15.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heard him scream a million times.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.20,0:03:18.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But in ten years of caring for him, this is the first time they've brought him to a hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.25,0:03:20.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,E.R. checked his throat. No obstructions, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.64,0:03:24.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means the only symptom was a scream, which is diagnostic of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.02,0:03:26.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid clutched his chest, B.P. was elevated.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.01,0:03:27.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe there was chest pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.09,0:03:29.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,E.R. said the heart was fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.01,0:03:30.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be so quick to dismiss pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.69,0:03:31.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are we going?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.63,0:03:32.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Down.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.94,0:03:34.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stool sample to check for parasites.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.81,0:03:36.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blood culture to rule out infection.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.43,0:03:38.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And ana for lupus.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.09,0:03:39.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because he screamed?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.51,0:03:41.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could also be an environmental reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.56,0:03:42.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An allergy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.42,0:03:43.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dust, wheat, pollen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.98,0:03:48.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A toxin, or something he ate.\NCheck the house and run a lung ventilation scan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.36,0:03:49.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lungs are in the chest too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.70,0:03:50.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had a date last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.64,0:03:51.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She screamed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.27,0:03:53.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Should we spend $100,000 testing her?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.18,0:03:54.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.00,0:03:55.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't a veterinary hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.89,0:03:57.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Zing!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.07,0:04:00.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, if you don't think this kid is worth saving-- that's not what I'm saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.12,0:04:00.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's too bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.82,0:04:01.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a good point.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.81,0:04:03.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid's just a lump with tonsils.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.09,0:04:07.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know what it's gonna be like ,trying to put an autistic kid into a nuclear scanner?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.52,0:04:09.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't envy you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.16,0:04:15.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want my old carpet back.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.51,0:04:18.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we're gonna have to do this later.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.25,0:04:19.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.44,0:04:21.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in the clinic had an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.04,0:04:25.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Generally, when people are on the-- I wanty old carpet back.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.89,0:04:27.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was stained with blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.28,0:04:28.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, my blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.52,0:04:29.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which makes the carpet part of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.00,0:04:31.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.05,0:04:32.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to be buried with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.19,0:04:36.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think you can get me to do anything you want, regardless of how stupid it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.30,0:04:37.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my office!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.61,0:04:39.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's where I work. Where I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.09,0:04:46.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where I save lives, allowing you to brag to rich people so they'll give you more money to spend on mris and low-cut tops.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.48,0:04:48.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want it back the way it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.07,0:04:50.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's identical to the old carpet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.75,0:04:53.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Except without the hazardous biological waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.18,0:04:59.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I shall not return to my office until every patented durable micro fiber has been restored to its rightful place.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.37,0:05:01.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspiring.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.71,0:05:03.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't want to work in your office,work in the clinic.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.83,0:05:05.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't want to work in the clinic,go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.38,0:05:06.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And don't get paid.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.34,0:05:12.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attica!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.06,0:05:17.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attica?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.25,0:05:23.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He,uh,just needs to finish this level.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.82,0:05:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We only have the scanner up for the next half hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.04,0:05:27.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After that-- trust me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.72,0:05:30.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't want to move him until he's finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.24,0:05:33.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sooner we do this test,the sooner we can get you guys home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.49,0:05:41.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Adam.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.59,0:05:45.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think that-- that we--
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.45,0:05:49.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ten minutes,tops.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.23,0:05:54.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he has a vascular disorder,he might not have that-- he might not have ten minutes?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.72,0:05:56.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have ten minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.15,0:05:59.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No,no,you don't-- want to do that--
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.11,0:06:01.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Adam. Adam.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.88,0:06:11.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I used metamucil like the doctor told me and finally I was able to use the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.87,0:06:17.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I saw something in the toilet I couldn't identify.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.18,0:06:22.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I wrapped it in tissue paper --so you could take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.45,0:06:28.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't you sedate him or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.06,0:06:31.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could if I didn't want the test results to mean anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.33,0:06:48.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Painkillers, exercising.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.59,0:06:51.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We even did that puncture thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.08,0:06:56.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing work then this morning, I get up, my back feels great.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.76,0:07:00.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I figured I'd betterget down here right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.72,0:07:12.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big shocker-- Dad's depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.63,0:07:13.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Save your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.87,0:07:16.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ssris don't cause chest pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.90,0:07:21.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every minute of every day is booked.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.75,0:07:24.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When he eats, sleeps, plays his handheld.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.55,0:07:26.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not much of a life for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.64,0:07:27.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They chose to have a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.73,0:07:30.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't get to decide what your kid's gonna be like.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.42,0:07:33.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody chooses this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.78,0:07:39.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.09,0:07:41.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You get a normal kid, the parent works.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.31,0:07:46.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You get a special kid that costs more, they quit and turn the backyard into a therapy circuit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.29,0:07:48.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes,if only you were handicapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.81,0:07:51.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the good times you could've had with dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.74,0:08:08.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi, Dr. House.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.77,0:08:14.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello ,girl whose name I don't remember, but whose dad I treated, so I don't really know why she's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.90,0:08:16.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ali.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.38,0:08:18.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, I think I caught what my dad has.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.95,0:08:20.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The rhino thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.86,0:08:22.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.83,0:08:25.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.76,0:08:27.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A little.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.10,0:08:30.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's in my chest,too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.23,0:08:31.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.27,0:08:43.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kinda had access through the shirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.70,0:08:45.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But... this'll work.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.08,0:08:51.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Feels good.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.67,0:08:56.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly when did New Jersey run out of horny 17-year-old boys?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.84,0:08:59.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About five weeks ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.41,0:09:01.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been very lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.55,0:09:12.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ventilation scan was normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.74,0:09:13.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Time to send him home.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.83,0:09:15.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't leave right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.59,0:09:16.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.53,0:09:19.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are the proud owner of your very own rhino thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.25,0:09:22.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A rhinovirus-- you can't leave because she has a cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.01,0:09:24.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't leave because Cuddy says I can't leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.68,0:09:30.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the tests are normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.60,0:09:32.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, don't start with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.39,0:09:33.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're backed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.29,0:09:36.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know this is hard for all of us, but thanks to Dr. Cuddy,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.57,0:09:37.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have an office.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.67,0:09:38.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I have to work here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.68,0:09:40.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What'd she do to your office?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.35,0:09:42.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's unusable.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.17,0:09:44.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So whatever is bothering him, it wasn't his lungs.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.66,0:09:45.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about the kid's house?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.58,0:09:48.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were some pesticides and some alcohol, but the tox screen was negative.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.60,0:09:50.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means there's nothing physically wrong with this kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.00,0:09:52.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We already had that discussion.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.48,0:09:53.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We get a fecal smear?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.81,0:09:55.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Should we do this someplace else?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.59,0:09:57.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, Cuddy says I have to work here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.80,0:10:01.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I said you can work in your office or you had to work here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.91,0:10:04.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And since I can't work in my office...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.41,0:10:06.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this your master plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.58,0:10:10.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Disrupt hospital business until I replace your carpet?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.48,0:10:11.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Devious.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.45,0:10:13.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Saw it in a James Bond movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.35,0:10:14.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fecal smear!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.64,0:10:16.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Talk to me.\N- Get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.75,0:10:18.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- You'll put back my carpet?\N- No.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.51,0:10:19.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.34,0:10:20.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fecal matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.12,0:10:21.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there a sample we can look at?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.80,0:10:23.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Parents have the smear kit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.16,0:10:24.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The kid is constipated.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.58,0:10:25.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do what you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.57,0:10:27.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not replacing your carpet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.93,0:10:32.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go up his rear and get a smear.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.08,0:10:34.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which reminds me, I kinda feel like a bagel.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.54,0:10:39.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Carpets.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.38,0:10:44.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We need a stool sample.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.66,0:10:49.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We should probably wait until he's finished playing that level, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.01,0:10:52.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I actually think he's a bit better today.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.06,0:10:53.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He seems more like his old self.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.71,0:10:55.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is possible that he was never sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.80,0:10:58.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess we, uh, could've overreacted.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.34,0:11:17.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what makes fluid fill the lining of a kid's lungs?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.01,0:11:18.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are we in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.87,0:11:20.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this some sort of power play?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.93,0:11:21.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.82,0:11:25.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you stuck your finger in the kid and gave him a pleural effusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.98,0:11:28.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You ever considered getting a manicure?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.10,0:11:30.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I took the stool sample after his lungs failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.42,0:11:32.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or do you really have a problem with the carpeting?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.13,0:11:35.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Change sets you off-- I said it was a power play.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.23,0:11:38.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone answers "yes" to option A, you don't move on to option B.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.15,0:11:40.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If there's a pleural effusion, we have to rule out heart failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.71,0:11:41.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why now?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.49,0:11:43.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why a power play now?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.08,0:11:44.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I smelled weakness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.93,0:11:47.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get the kid an echocardiogram.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.02,0:11:55.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's... funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.07,0:11:59.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It says "James Wilson." A strange typo.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.40,0:12:04.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the fluid comes back an exudate, get him on broad-spectrum antibiotics.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.72,0:12:06.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.55,0:12:07.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.47,0:12:11.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thought you wouldn't mind sharing offices for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.05,0:12:14.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You share stories, feelings...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.76,0:12:16.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Toys.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.39,0:12:18.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't share offices.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.05,0:12:20.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is so not zen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.15,0:12:22.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.99,0:12:24.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some doctors get those.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.44,0:12:25.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you want mornings or afternoons?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.95,0:12:31.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You couldn't make Cuddy miserable, so you're gonna make me miserable so I can make Cuddy miserable on your behalf?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.01,0:12:32.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.82,0:12:34.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What makes you think I can make her miserable?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.89,0:12:36.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you're good at that stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.08,0:12:38.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm nothing compared to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.13,0:12:39.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there anything you'll throw out?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.42,0:12:41.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a gift from an 11-year-old patient of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.76,0:12:45.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She and I both knew it was a piece of junk, and that's what made her laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.02,0:12:50.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you gotta keep it until she-- she already did.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.50,0:13:00.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Adam.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.30,0:13:02.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need you to stay still, buddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.23,0:13:03.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's okay, it's okay. I got him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.94,0:13:08.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.05,0:13:10.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.04,0:13:18.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.07,0:13:20.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it? Is his heart okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.22,0:13:22.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.29,0:13:29.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Echo suggested a conduction abnormality.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.53,0:13:31.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,EKG confirmed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.05,0:13:33.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still doesn't explain the effusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.58,0:13:35.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The pleural fluid was an exudate.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.38,0:13:38.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We should be looking for something that explains both the heart and lung problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.45,0:13:40.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Infection, parasite, cancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.77,0:13:45.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Microbiology showed no organisms in the fluid, so forget infection.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.64,0:13:47.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not a power play.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.21,0:13:51.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doing a differential in the clinic makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.55,0:13:52.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Piss Cuddy off.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.54,0:13:53.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Same thing with Wilson's office.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.74,0:13:54.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Works indirectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.90,0:13:57.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But now, we are in office space.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.41,0:14:00.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you don't want to be in your own office.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.18,0:14:02.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means this has nothing to do with Cuddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.75,0:14:05.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really are obsessed with your carpets.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.05,0:14:07.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means-- What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.81,0:14:10.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have this room booked from 2:00 to 3:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.20,0:14:13.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, 2:00 east coast time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.51,0:14:16.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you meant Pacific.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.10,0:14:17.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which is...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.04,0:14:19.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stupid of me, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.22,0:14:22.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about parasites?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.40,0:14:23.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stool sample was negative.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.80,0:14:24.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's 2:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.95,0:14:27.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, well, we should go, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.81,0:14:29.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That just leaves cancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.84,0:14:30.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get a lung biopsy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.00,0:14:33.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It took a half an hour to get the mask on the kid for the lung scan.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.83,0:14:34.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.63,0:14:37.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was there somewhere you needed to be?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.00,0:14:42.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,House.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.67,0:14:44.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can we talk?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.86,0:14:50.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Carpet?\N- Never.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.44,0:14:51.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing to talk about.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.67,0:14:55.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your girlfriend called the clinic 15 times looking for you today.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.01,0:14:56.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lot to discuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.95,0:14:58.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,China patterns-- House.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.13,0:14:59.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's a stalker.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.31,0:15:00.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.25,0:15:01.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't be that she finds me interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.89,0:15:02.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attractive.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.79,0:15:03.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Has to be that she's insane.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.88,0:15:05.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's called you 15 times.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.80,0:15:07.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your mother's not that interested in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.14,0:15:09.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, maybe I'd be better adjusted if she was.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.19,0:15:11.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- I'm notifying security.\N- Is this about the carpet?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.36,0:15:13.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think I'll back off if you block all my fun?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.18,0:15:14.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You better not be having fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.54,0:15:15.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm having fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.35,0:15:16.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not having sex.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.36,0:15:18.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- She's dangerous.\N- She's not dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.06,0:15:18.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.93,0:15:19.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.78,0:15:21.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Men are stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.08,0:15:22.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm with you so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.04,0:15:23.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm notifying security.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.74,0:15:25.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, give her a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.46,0:15:27.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's not dangerous, she's...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.84,0:15:29.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,insightful.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.21,0:15:33.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't stop our love!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.50,0:15:39.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you got a minute?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.79,0:15:40.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.53,0:15:44.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have a ten-year-old with pleural effusion and conduction abnormality but no heart failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.78,0:15:46.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was there a protein in the pleural fluid?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.38,0:15:48.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's why we're thinking cancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.34,0:15:49.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Non-hodgkin's, probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.60,0:15:51.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So we want to do a lung biopsy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.66,0:15:53.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lung biopsies usually come back negative.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.41,0:15:55.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So biopsy a lymph node under the arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.53,0:15:57.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's probably something an oncologist should do, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.96,0:15:59.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing real tricky to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.22,0:16:00.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a biopsy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.08,0:16:03.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, just to be safe, you mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.08,0:16:12.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For the love of god!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.94,0:16:15.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't somebody shut that kid up?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.63,0:16:17.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some people are trying to work around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.43,0:16:19.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you show him a teddy bear or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.36,0:16:20.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.28,0:16:22.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Somebody you'll never send a a gift to.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.17,0:16:23.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Dr. House.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.35,0:16:24.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your son's doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.86,0:16:26.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,High test, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.73,0:16:29.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey, hey, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.14,0:16:35.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Out of vicodin?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.58,0:16:37.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.17,0:16:40.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eating the red berries.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.84,0:17:08.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He trusted you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.47,0:17:11.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that wasn't trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.07,0:17:11.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.83,0:17:12.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,self-preservation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.89,0:17:13.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.61,0:17:15.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.60,0:17:17.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was like a conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.44,0:17:24.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A monk-- a monkey's afraid to eat the red berries until he sees another monkey eat them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.56,0:17:26.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Monkey see, monkey do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.22,0:17:27.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.31,0:17:32.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your kid's still just as messed up as when we admitted him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.49,0:17:46.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was sensitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.91,0:17:49.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have pretty hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.20,0:17:53.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hope is all those parents have going for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.12,0:17:56.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, hope is what's making them miserable.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.14,0:17:59.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What they should do is get a cocker spaniel.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.34,0:18:01.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A dog would look them in the eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.31,0:18:02.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wag his tail when he's happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.01,0:18:04.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lick their face, show them love.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.76,0:18:07.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it so wrong for them to want to have a normal child?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.13,0:18:09.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's normal to want to be normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.14,0:18:12.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spoken likea true circle queen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.08,0:18:17.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See, skinny, socially privileged white people get to draw this neat little circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.67,0:18:20.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And everyone inside the circle is normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.54,0:18:26.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone outside the circle should be beaten, broken and reset so they can be brought into the circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.79,0:18:29.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Failing that, they should be institutionalized.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.31,0:18:30.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or worse, pitied.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.96,0:18:33.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it's wrong to feel sorry for this little boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.18,0:18:37.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you feel sorry for someone who gets to opt out of the inane courteous formalities?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.36,0:18:41.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which are utterly meaningless, insincere and therefore degrading?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.08,0:18:47.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This kid doesn't have to pretend to be interested in your back pain, or your excretions, or your grandma's itchy place.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.57,0:18:53.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you imagine how liberating it would be to live a life free of all the mind-numbing social niceties?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.58,0:18:56.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't pity this kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.66,0:18:58.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I envy him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.15,0:19:01.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, no cancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.74,0:19:02.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.77,0:19:04.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These aren't lymph cells.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.61,0:19:06.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.21,0:19:09.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Liver cells.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.52,0:19:20.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Liver cells under his arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.22,0:19:25.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wonder what he's got whereh is liver's supposed to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.25,0:19:43.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone got a clue how liver cells got into the kid's armpit?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.19,0:19:49.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Make yourself at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.70,0:19:53.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, you think maybe Grey's Anatomy got it all wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.44,0:19:56.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lymph system circulates fluid, not organ cells.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.12,0:19:58.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cancer cells break into the lymphatic system all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.45,0:20:00.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we're not talking about cancer cells.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.03,0:20:02.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the difference between cancer cells and liver cells?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.61,0:20:04.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why can one pass through walls but the other can't?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.89,0:20:05.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cancer cells are damaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.76,0:20:06.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lets them grow into blood vessels.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.80,0:20:08.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go wherever they want.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.08,0:20:10.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So if the liver cells are damaged-- liver isn't damaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.57,0:20:11.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The tests were normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.76,0:20:17.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So if the liver cells are damaged, it's theoretically possible to pass into the lymphatic system.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.17,0:20:20.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Liver failure could also explain pleural effusion, even the heart issues.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.28,0:20:21.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Liver cells are fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.48,0:20:27.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was immunized for hep A and B, and do you really think this kid is having unprotected sex or sharing needles?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.80,0:20:30.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Daddy does seem the type to use a rubber.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.76,0:20:32.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it's not viral.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.55,0:20:35.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That just leaves "lotta-booze-irrhosis".
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.45,0:20:39.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our ten-year-old boy does not have a drinking problem or cirrhosis.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.47,0:20:42.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,House, when we echoed his heart, we got a piece of his liver-- there was no scarring.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.52,0:20:43.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cirrhosis explains the symptoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.98,0:20:46.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heart problems, lungs-- look up "cirrhosis" in the dictionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.52,0:20:47.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It means "scarring".
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.65,0:20:50.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Parents aren't doing or dosing this kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.10,0:20:51.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How would you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.35,0:20:52.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid can't talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.55,0:20:53.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why'd you think I took this case?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.80,0:20:55.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not gonna give away the ending.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.29,0:20:56.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They quit their jobs for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.83,0:21:00.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, they are everything you'd want in a parent.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.31,0:21:03.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, their kid is nothing you'd want.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.69,0:21:06.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When a baby is born, it's perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.37,0:21:08.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Little fingers, little toes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.47,0:21:10.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plump, perfect, pink.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.67,0:21:13.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And brimming with unbridled potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.77,0:21:15.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But then it's downhill.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.39,0:21:17.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some hills steeper than others.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.06,0:21:22.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Parents get off on their kids' accomplishments-- (toy)Bend over and relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.32,0:21:23.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.99,0:21:27.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They'll annoy you with trophy rooms and report cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.61,0:21:32.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hell, they'll even show you a purple cow and tell you what a keen eye for color their kid has.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.61,0:21:41.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But this kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.61,0:21:44.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't smile, he doesn't hug them, he doesn't laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.59,0:21:48.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His parents get nothing-- the right to brag that their kid picked orange juice out of a lineup.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.96,0:21:52.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you figure they slip the kid a mickey so they don't have to deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.64,0:21:54.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do a biopsy to confirm cirrhosis.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.76,0:21:58.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And don't try and pawn it off on Wilson-- he's gonna be busy with Cuddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.13,0:22:06.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My parents loved me unconditionally.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.34,0:22:08.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.23,0:22:13.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think the restraining order's a little much?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.72,0:22:16.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not actually going to have sex with a 17-year-old patient.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.57,0:22:20.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think he was gonna ask me to dig a blood stained carpet out of a dumpster, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.58,0:22:23.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It might be easier in the long run.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.31,0:22:29.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are we stopping here so House doesn't find us?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.69,0:22:31.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unless you want to make out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.21,0:22:35.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You want me to surrender to House's coup?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.18,0:22:38.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, you proactively...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.45,0:22:41.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give him what he wants.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.17,0:22:43.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I defeat him by surrendering to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.10,0:22:44.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He'll never see it coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.51,0:22:46.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, I'll pay for it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.18,0:22:48.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, a thousand bucks to carpet a room?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.31,0:22:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, it's 400.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.60,0:22:52.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh-- Not doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.14,0:22:59.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Liver biopsy?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.92,0:23:00.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're doing it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.96,0:23:02.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How's it going?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.36,0:23:03.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like a biopsy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.53,0:23:04.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Needles, cells.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.89,0:23:06.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Screaming.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.26,0:23:08.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What'd you findin the stool sample?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.05,0:23:12.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were too busy bothering Cuddy, but as discussed, it was negative for parasites.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.40,0:23:13.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can we get out of here?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.67,0:23:15.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't ask what you didn't find.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.18,0:23:17.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I asked what you did find in the stool sample.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.18,0:23:18.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stool.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.18,0:23:21.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And traces of iron, zinc, calcium carbonate.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.92,0:23:22.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can we leave?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.75,0:23:23.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.56,0:23:25.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You afraid of the man?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.94,0:23:30.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.10,0:23:33.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave my stuff alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.85,0:23:36.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have a meeting with a Guggenheim in 15 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.08,0:23:37.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wearing that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.27,0:23:40.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna count to three, and then I'm gonna fire you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.33,0:23:43.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- One.\N- Calcium carbonate, that's an antidiarrheal, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.61,0:23:45.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Two.\N- You think that's significant?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.31,0:23:48.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think hard poops is significant?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.98,0:23:51.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two and a half?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.40,0:23:53.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Never threaten unless you're ready to deliver.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.70,0:23:55.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Makes you look weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.05,0:23:57.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank god you don't have children.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.32,0:24:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Cuddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.62,0:24:05.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take a message.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.95,0:24:10.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your patient is being rushed to cardiac ICU.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.68,0:24:14.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's like the one thing that would get me outta here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.32,0:24:17.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, you can't come in here now.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.36,0:24:19.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.10,0:24:25.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's in v-fib.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.40,0:24:31.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.86,0:24:32.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Charging.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.56,0:24:33.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.69,0:24:34.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Charging.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.49,0:24:35.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.78,0:24:36.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Charging.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.63,0:24:37.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.92,0:24:51.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's stable for the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.62,0:24:53.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First-degree atrial ventricular block.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.96,0:24:55.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.18,0:24:56.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What else do we know?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.22,0:24:59.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His liver's damaged, pleural effusion compromised his lung function.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.32,0:25:01.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,biopsy was negative for cirrhosis.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.62,0:25:04.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Parents didn't poison their son.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.94,0:25:08.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not his liver, his heart, or his lungs.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.55,0:25:10.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the calcium carbonate in his stool.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.88,0:25:11.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid was constipated.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.81,0:25:13.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Parents probably just overdid it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.63,0:25:15.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or they didn't do it at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.89,0:25:18.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calcium carbonate's also what's in chalk.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.03,0:25:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he ate some chalk.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.34,0:25:22.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't toxic-- Sure didn't cause the pleural effusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.13,0:25:23.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forget the chalk.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.11,0:25:24.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just said it was about the chalk.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.30,0:25:26.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, and then I said, "forget the chalk".
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.33,0:25:28.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must be very confused.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.10,0:25:29.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This kid's got pica.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.78,0:25:32.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take him to a buffet, he's gonna eat the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.21,0:25:33.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or lead paint.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.25,0:25:34.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Level of lead in the blood was normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.84,0:25:35.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His tox screen was clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.75,0:25:37.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're not looking for typical poisons.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.27,0:25:39.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're looking for anything that he can put in his mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.45,0:25:41.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Matches, spiders, bricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.37,0:25:43.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pressure-treated wood used to contain arsenic.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.02,0:25:45.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even better.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.34,0:25:45.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hansel?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.98,0:25:47.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get samples of the ginger bread house.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.76,0:25:49.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bag everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.73,0:26:06.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You could get into a lot of trouble,being here.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.00,0:26:08.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.44,0:26:09.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I got that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.98,0:26:13.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So did everyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.22,0:26:15.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They think you're a stalker.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.03,0:26:18.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One could argue those people might be jealous of your attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.23,0:26:21.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes,I actually made that argument.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.04,0:26:23.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You going home?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.73,0:26:25.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.46,0:26:30.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In Iceland, the age of consent is 14.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.16,0:26:33.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surprised that tourism isn't a bigger industry up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.78,0:26:35.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So today I'm jailbait.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.94,0:26:37.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But in 22 weeks...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.06,0:26:41.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anybody can do anything to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.46,0:26:45.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will I be so different in 22 weeks?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.50,0:26:48.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,22 weeks is enough for an embryo to grow arms and legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.59,0:26:50.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a line.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.71,0:26:54.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An arbitrary line drawn by a bunch of sad, old men in robes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.22,0:26:55.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.23,0:26:57.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who cares what judges think?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.68,0:27:03.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't think of youas a guy who followed rules just because they were rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.17,0:27:11.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are... over ten years younger than me.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.30,0:27:14.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said over.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.17,0:27:18.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gotta go!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.21,0:27:19.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,House.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.88,0:27:21.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Cuddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.01,0:27:24.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you happen to know the way to the Icelandic consulate?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.16,0:27:28.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This young woman, a stranger to me, was just asking directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.13,0:27:29.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Security was gonna call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.96,0:27:31.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to do that to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.36,0:27:32.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.24,0:27:33.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She needed a ride.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.27,0:27:36.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She got her on her own, she can get home on her own.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.26,0:27:39.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.17,0:27:44.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if I see you on hospital grounds again, I will call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.49,0:28:00.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After that look, I'm feeling a little frisky.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.68,0:28:02.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like you're up.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.07,0:28:04.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm ovulating. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.48,0:28:07.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The frisky, it went away.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.61,0:28:10.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,House, this isn't a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.80,0:28:18.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I leave her alone, can I have my carpet back?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.13,0:28:19.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.13,0:28:23.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I forget about my carpet, can I have her?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.69,0:28:49.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jimsonweed.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.74,0:28:52.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Found a small patch of it in his backyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.45,0:28:54.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jimsonweed contains atropine.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.61,0:28:56.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Poor man's acid.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.09,0:28:59.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our kid's been tripping on Lucy in the sky with cubic zirconia.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.66,0:29:02.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Explains the pleural effusion, the heart arrhythmias.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.06,0:29:04.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meeting here will do nothing to upset Cuddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.04,0:29:05.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not trying to upset Cuddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.25,0:29:07.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm trying to figure out what's wrong with the patient.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.72,0:29:08.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.79,0:29:09.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm done.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.45,0:29:11.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jimsonweed doesn't explain the screaming.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.06,0:29:13.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've obviously never had a bad trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.80,0:29:16.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would've thought you'd try to accomplish two goals at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.20,0:29:19.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't you be more like the other age-in appropriate girls who have a thing for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.80,0:29:21.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just accept me for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.98,0:29:23.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.78,0:29:27.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Treatment for jimsonweed od is physostigmine.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.60,0:29:28.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid's got heart issues.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.75,0:29:29.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The two don't mix.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.82,0:29:31.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'd better make sure that's what he's got.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.23,0:29:34.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Serum from the lab in paterson is three days, minimum.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.24,0:29:36.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He won't survive three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.60,0:29:38.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What time does he wake up?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.10,0:29:39.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,7:35 am.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.05,0:29:40.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.97,0:29:41.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Walk me through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.85,0:29:44.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,7:40 to 7:50, he goes to the toilet, washes his face.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.97,0:29:45.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does this matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.84,0:29:47.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm trying to prove he ate the plant.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.19,0:29:49.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His schedule has nothing to do with jimsonweed.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.29,0:29:52.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are two possibilities-- either the parents saw him eat the plant,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.38,0:29:56.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or the kid has unsupervised time and eats plants instead of playing with blocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.51,0:30:00.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you find 15 minutes of free time outside, doesn't mean he spent it eating a bush.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.72,0:30:01.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.67,0:30:02.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.48,0:30:03.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait for the kid to tell us?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.75,0:30:05.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.36,0:30:10.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.12,0:30:12.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To talk to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.38,0:30:25.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever see your son eat a bush?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.67,0:30:26.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.39,0:30:27.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've only ever seen him eat what--
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.88,0:30:30.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Adam, you ate something at your house.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.09,0:30:31.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something that made you sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.89,0:30:34.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need you to show me what you ate.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.44,0:30:35.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He can't answer you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.91,0:30:37.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Neither can you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.42,0:30:41.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is your backyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.05,0:30:43.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You may know it as Mel's diner.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.53,0:30:45.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is your sandbox.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.63,0:30:47.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your jungle gym.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.55,0:30:50.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And under it is this.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.65,0:30:55.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to know if you ate this, Adam.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.56,0:30:57.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't know what you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.88,0:30:59.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Adam, you have to tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.17,0:31:02.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because if you don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.72,0:31:06.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be game over.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.73,0:31:09.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- You'll be dead.\N- What the hell are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.02,0:31:11.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Show me what you ate.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.90,0:31:12.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Adam.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.75,0:31:16.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Show me what you ate.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.66,0:31:31.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sandbox
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.54,0:31:38.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Adam?\N- Honey?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.34,0:31:39.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Adam?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.55,0:31:52.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on in, brothers and sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.95,0:31:55.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome to the house of the lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.06,0:31:56.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,House, come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.55,0:31:57.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The chapel?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.28,0:32:01.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have been blessed with the miracle of a new symptom.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.35,0:32:07.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brother, can you testify as to why this poor child's eyeball rolled back into his head?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.90,0:32:11.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's consistent with jimsonweed poisoning-- ocular paralysis.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.50,0:32:12.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.08,0:32:16.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The wicked shall deceive ye, because they have turned from the Lord and are idiots.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.85,0:32:19.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His ocular muscle didn't paralyze, it pirouetted.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.41,0:32:20.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,M.S.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.23,0:32:23.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is easier for a wise man to gain access to heaven
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.38,0:32:25.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you stop doing that? Just say "not M.S".
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.93,0:32:26.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A stroke.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.88,0:32:28.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bleed in the brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.11,0:32:31.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'd be seeing other symptoms besides a single eye misalignment.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.46,0:32:32.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like a coma.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.16,0:32:33.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you've already testified.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.52,0:32:34.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a tumor.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.21,0:32:37.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And all the imaging just missed it?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.10,0:32:38.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a microtumor.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.68,0:32:40.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Started in his lung, which caused the pleural effusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.95,0:32:44.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then it metastasized to his liver, which made it slough cells.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.03,0:32:48.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then went to his brain, behind the eye, which caused it to roll back into his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.47,0:32:52.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he has three tumors and we missed all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.03,0:32:53.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the opposite of a miracle?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.33,0:32:57.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a better chance of finding it now that I know exactly where to look.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.18,0:32:58.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.54,0:33:02.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unless you have a better idea, I'm gonna go CT his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.74,0:33:07.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then, if--if I have to, remove his eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.78,0:33:16.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You remove this kid's eye, he's only gonna behalf as good at not making eye contact.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.90,0:33:28.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.84,0:33:31.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.67,0:33:34.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.13,0:33:37.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have sad news for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.80,0:33:39.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She doesn't love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.40,0:33:41.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're ugly when you're jealous.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.17,0:33:43.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She showed up at my house last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.05,0:33:45.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Came on to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.11,0:33:46.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's even more perfect than I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.93,0:33:48.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,House.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.29,0:33:49.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.87,0:33:52.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You say "sick", I say "freestylin'".
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.42,0:33:54.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The girl will have sex with an invertebrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.83,0:33:55.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.51,0:33:57.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not that bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.54,0:33:59.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She has a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.10,0:34:01.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not doing her any favors by indulging her.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.10,0:34:02.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you lie like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.88,0:34:04.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you not have room your heart for love?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.89,0:34:06.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.19,0:34:09.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't believe the kids when they said that Susie was sleeping with Johnny.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.05,0:34:10.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't believe them then, I don't believe them now.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.46,0:34:13.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care that Susie married Johnny-- he's mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.69,0:34:17.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She has a mole on her right breast, just below the nipple.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.90,0:34:19.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, she doesn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.05,0:34:20.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've seen her breasts?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.30,0:34:21.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a medical exam.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.67,0:34:22.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was listening to her heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.80,0:34:27.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It went, "Greg-House, Greg-House, Greg-House."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.85,0:34:29.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, I'm lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.96,0:34:31.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But she did come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.91,0:34:33.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's locked up in my office.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.84,0:34:35.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was hoping you could talk to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.62,0:34:37.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Put an end to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.07,0:34:54.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.94,0:35:00.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any idea what you'd have to look forward to if you stayed with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.32,0:35:04.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nine chances out of ten, we'd both wind up in a jail.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.86,0:35:07.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're only saying that to make me go.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.66,0:35:10.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm saying it 'cause it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.64,0:35:16.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inside of us, we both know that you belong with Victor.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.86,0:35:20.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there a Victor in your class?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.23,0:35:28.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're not with someone your age, you'll regret it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.17,0:35:31.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe not today, maybe not tomorrow, but soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.05,0:35:33.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And for the rest of your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.65,0:35:36.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about us?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.55,0:35:39.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll always have Fresno.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.48,0:35:42.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm no good at being noble,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.77,0:35:49.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it doesn't take much to see that the problems of two little people dot amount to a hill of beans in this crazy world.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.74,0:35:54.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someday you'll understand that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.11,0:35:57.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.33,0:36:00.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's looking at you...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.58,0:36:08.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.29,0:36:11.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was there an earthquake when you were in Fresno?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.02,0:36:13.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.02,0:36:15.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I ask all my girlfriends that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.35,0:36:20.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, a little one.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.36,0:36:22.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.99,0:36:23.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.90,0:36:24.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.87,0:36:26.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not love.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.39,0:36:29.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have a spore in your brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.76,0:36:31.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Coccidioides immitis.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.68,0:36:32.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,California's full of 'em.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.97,0:36:36.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They get an earthquake, they get released into the air, you breathe it in, you get a cold...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.92,0:36:39.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turns into sinus congestion, aches, weakness...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.59,0:36:40.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Milky tears...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.85,0:36:43.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And sometimes...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.82,0:36:47.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A loss of inhibition and judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.58,0:36:49.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.31,0:36:50.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.57,0:36:52.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,loving you?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.29,0:36:54.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wanting to have sex with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.69,0:36:56.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was all just...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.16,0:36:58.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the spores talking?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.40,0:37:04.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll probably live.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.58,0:37:09.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.29,0:37:34.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.80,0:37:36.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't touch his eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.89,0:37:39.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is an appendectomy.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.52,0:37:44.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like i said, don't touch his eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.70,0:37:48.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why isn't he in surgery?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.01,0:37:50.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, some emergency bumped him.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.06,0:37:51.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've got another room in ten minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.42,0:37:53.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not taking him in.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.26,0:37:54.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kill the lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.29,0:37:59.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was seeing them all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.44,0:38:01.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.20,0:38:02.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And he was telling us what he was seeing.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.82,0:38:05.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Telling us exactly what was wrong with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.40,0:38:08.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Drawing them for us over and over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.29,0:38:10.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody knew how to speak "autistic".
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.23,0:38:13.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I asked him what he ate, he even told me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.36,0:38:14.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.21,0:38:16.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was he seeing?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.14,0:38:20.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, my pretties.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.64,0:38:22.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not a tumor, Foreman.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.38,0:38:23.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's worms.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.30,0:38:25.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Swimming in his eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.51,0:38:29.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Animal makes potty in the sandbox.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.10,0:38:32.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Boy plays in the sandbox, boy eats the sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.39,0:38:34.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can probably tell where this is going by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.35,0:38:36.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stool samples were negative for parasites.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.04,0:38:38.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Raccoon roundworms are not excreted by their human host.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.99,0:38:40.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cameron tested the sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.38,0:38:41.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.21,0:38:44.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Worms spread from his gut to the rest of his body.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.78,0:38:45.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They attacked his lungs.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.85,0:38:48.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what made him scream and caused the effusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.26,0:38:51.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They invade his liver, sending dead liver cells coursing through his system.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.93,0:38:57.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They attack his eyeand the muscles surrounding it, making his eyeball do a backflip.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.67,0:39:02.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Laser photocoagulation to fix the eye and a high dose of benzimidazole to kill the worms.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.79,0:39:03.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.87,0:39:04.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.88,0:39:06.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-he's gonna be okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.15,0:39:08.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.66,0:39:12.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's gonna be with you for a long, long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.66,0:39:21.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to read you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.87,0:39:25.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Asperger's syndrome is a mild and rare form of autism".
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.14,0:39:30.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"It is typically characterized by difficulty establishing friendshipsand playing with peers,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.28,0:39:36.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,trouble accepting convential social rules, and they dislike any change in setting or routine."
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.97,0:39:38.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or broadloom.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.61,0:39:40.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't say that last part, but you get my point.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.77,0:39:42.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,House doesn't have Asperger's.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.22,0:39:44.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The diagnosisis much simpler.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.28,0:39:45.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a jerk.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.37,0:39:47.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you think he took this case?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.28,0:39:49.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because he believes these parents?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.03,0:39:51.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because he wants to help a young boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.25,0:39:54.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sees himself in this kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.20,0:39:57.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And he's trying to help himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.39,0:40:00.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't want this.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.55,0:40:02.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He needs it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.25,0:40:18.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not autistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.91,0:40:20.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't even have Asperger's.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.45,0:40:21.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You wish you did.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.84,0:40:23.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would exempt you from the rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.98,0:40:27.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give you freedom, absolve you of responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.11,0:40:29.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let you date 17-year-olds.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.19,0:40:32.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But most important, it would mean that you're not just a jerk.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.73,0:40:38.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At what point does a person endlessly lecturing someone make him a jerk?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.31,0:40:47.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your first tongue kiss...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.93,0:40:51.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An eight on the happiness scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.33,0:40:55.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your child being snatched back from the brink of death...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.62,0:40:57.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.58,0:41:04.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But they're clocking in at a very tepid 6.5,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.89,0:41:08.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because they know what they have to go back to.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.80,0:41:15.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, listen...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.73,0:41:19.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.85,0:41:22.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You saved his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.25,0:41:23.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.85,0:41:25.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See ya.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.76,0:42:21.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was so good.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.89,0:42:35.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was a ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.89,0:42:58.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All change is bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.13,0:43:01.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not true, you know.
